author: John Jurgensen
title: HBO Trounces Rivals at the Emmy Awards
text:
HBO torched the competition at the 67th Primetime Emmy Awards and proved its continuing potency in a fast-changing television landscape. The network swept the ceremony’s top awards Sunday night with wins for the comedy “Veep” and the drama “Game of Thrones.”
Both shows dominated their respective fields, with other wins for acting, writing and directing. “Game of Thrones” set a record for winning the most Emmys of any series in a single year.
